Subject: MDKSA-2004:161 - Updated xpdf packages fix buffer overflow vulnerability


-----BEGIN PGP SIGNED MESSAGE-----
Hash: SHA1

 _______________________________________________________________________

                 Mandrakelinux Security Update Advisory
 _______________________________________________________________________

 Package name:           xpdf
 Advisory ID:            MDKSA-2004:161
 Date:                   December 29th, 2004

 Affected versions:	 10.0, 10.1, Corporate Server 2.1
 ______________________________________________________________________

 Problem Description:

 iDefense reported a buffer overflow vulnerability, which affects 
 versions of xpdf <= xpdf-3.0. An attacker could construct a malicious 
 payload file which could enable arbitrary code execution on the target 
 system.
 
 The updated packages are patched to protect against these
 vulnerabilities.
 _______________________________________________________________________

 References:

  http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CAN-2004-1125
 ______________________________________________________________________

